tags: Wait time,
review:
We travelled from far distance and booked appointment at 11.00 am. We have reached on time. But still the receptionist was saying we need to wait for 2 hours for health examination by another doctor then after Dr. Narmda will have a look over patient.
Its quiet upsetting o wait for such a long time without any reason.
Patients should be treated as quickly as possible. Waiting for no reason makes no meaning. 
And receptionist should behave properly with the patients.

Hope this will be considered on high priority and reduce the waiting time.
reply_text:
Thank you for your feedback. Negative feedbacks help us make changes for improvement. 

We reviewed events on the day. Appointment was 11:00. When you arrived, you were explained the process which is correct. Dr Narmada will see the patients after minimum initial information is gathered by another member of staff which is for time efficiency. 

But 2 hours waiting was a wrong information given to you. We took action and trained the member of staff not to mislead patients.

We run our clinic on ‚Äúappointment only‚Äù basis - 20 to 30 minutes per patient based on what they are coming for. 

Sometimes unfortunately there can be a delay if the patient before you is inconsiderate of your time and takes longer or a 11 am patient comes at 11:20 and eats away time from the patient booked at 11.20. 

Your feedback is taken as high priority to give accurate information to patients. 

Happy to help of your problem isn‚Äôt resolved yet. Please be there few minutes before the schedule to facility registration. 

Many thanks

review: I visited Genesis clinic in late 2020, and met Dr. Narmada madam. She diagnosed and explained me about my medical condition and I came to know that I was suffering from severe endometriosis leading to infertility problems. We, as a couple, appeared for various counselling sessions to find out the best treatment for us. Dr. Narmada was extremely kind and friendly and she invested significant amount of sessions to explore all the available treatments and explained the best one suited for us. We decided to undergo IVF procedures and I conceived twins at the very first cycle. Finally that moment came and today, I am a mother of twin boys. I would highly recommend couples undergoing infertility problems to visit Genesis, meet Dr. Narmada and undergo the treatments recommended by her.
reply_text: We are so happy for you üòä Congratulations and best wishes to the twins üòä

reply_text:
So sorry for the experience you had and that you had to leave even before being seen by a doctor. We were informed about your leaving the premises only after you left. I can only sincerely apologise. 

A team member takes the history and then Dr Narmada reviews the woman/couple and completes the treatment plan. We do provide a detailed, organised and personalised care to all our patients and in that process, unfortunately we do take a little more time. However, it definitely doesn‚Äôt take 2 hours for registration. We give tablet to those who can enter details or a paper copy and staff help in filing it.

We couldn‚Äôt even enquire the reason for your attendance as the male front office staff are not authorised to ask symptoms. And a medical staff didn‚Äôt get an opportunity to meet you. 

We are happy to help in case your issue isn‚Äôt resolved. And once again, sorry for your experience.

Thank you your feedback. And I am so sorry that you had to wait. We are trying our best to speed up the waiting but unfortunately due to COVID pandemic, we are thin on the ground due to staff absences. We extremely apologise for the long wait you had and will ensure to minimise delays. 

And coming to process, I hope you understand senior doctor can move through the clinic sooner once history taking is completed by the juniors. If senior doctor does that task too, delays will be even longer 

We are proud to say that our rate of successful treatment got heavy periods without performing the surgery is very high. Hope your problem was resolved too.
